# Fixture for rule cif.value.invalid_uncertainty (issue #18).
# CIF numeric values may carry a standard-uncertainty suffix of the form
# <number>(<digits>), e.g. 12.34(5). The values below use malformed suffixes:
# - non-numeric content inside the parentheses: 12.34(ab)
# - decimal inside the parentheses:            12.34(5.6)
# - empty parentheses:                         12.34()
# - a stray trailing character:                1.2(3)x
data_invalid_uncertainty
_cell_length_a 12.34(ab)
_cell_length_b 12.34(5.6)
_cell_length_c 12.34()
_cell_angle_alpha 1.2(3)x
_cell_angle_beta  9.81(2)
